in the tetrahedral sites which may block Li-conduction

Notably, air-protected sample holders can only limit atmos-
pheric contact, thus, intermediate states have been observed to
arise (see the Supporting Information). Despite the improve-
ment in symmetry, distortion is still observed for LZLGO_300
air exposed. The lowering of symmetry compared to
LZLGO_150 and LZLGO_200 analogues probably implies
some degree of Li ordering in the structure that leads to a
partial tetragonal distortion and, therefore, an important drop
in conductivity of nearly 2 orders of magnitude.
